006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from a place in Hampshire, so called from an unattested short form of Old English <i>popel</i> ‘pebble’ + Old English <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’.","History: The Popham Colony was the first organized attempt to establish an English colony on the shores of what is now known as New England, then called Northern Virginia. George Popham of Hunstworth, Somerset, England, helped establish the colony at the mouth of the Kennebec River in 1607. It lasted for little over a year until it was abandoned in 1608. Although George died that same year, he may have had descendants or relatives with him as there are Pophams in the US who trace their family roots to the colony."],"variants":[{"name":"Poplin","meanings":["English: at least in part, a variant of   Popham  ."]}]},{"name":"Gilbert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. This was the name of the founder of the only native British religious order (abolished at the Dissolution of the Monasteries),  St Gilbert  of Sempringham (  ?1083–1189 ), in whose honour it is still sometimes bestowed, especially among Roman Catholics. It gained a wider currency in the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":59,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":68,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Gilbert de Popham was born about 1156, in Popham, Hampshire, England. He married Joan Clarke about 1192. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died on 4 November 1251, in Basingstoke, Hampshire, England, at the age of 96."},"et":{"about 1156–4 November 1251":"umbes 1156–4. november 1251","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1187–1251":"1187–1251","1187–Male":"1187–Surnud","1195–1225":"1195–1225","1156–1251":"1156–1251","4 November 1251":"4. november 1251","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1156":"1156","circa 1192":"umbes 1192","1187":"1187","about 1156":"umbes 1156","1251":"1251","1195":"1195","about 1187":"umbes 1187","1160":"1160","Lymington, Hampshire, England":"Lymington, Hampshire, England","Basingstoke, Hampshire, England":"Basingstoke, Hampshire, England","England":"England","Popham, Hampshire, England":"Popham, Hampshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1156–4 November 1251":"noin 1156–4. marraskuuta 1251","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1187–1251":"1187–1251","1187–Male":"1187–Kuollut","1195–1225":"1195–1225","1156–1251":"1156–1251","4 November 1251":"4. marraskuuta 1251","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1156":"1156","circa 1192":"noin 1192","1187":"1187","about 1156":"noin 1156","1251":"1251","1195":"1195","about 1187":"noin 1187","1160":"1160","Lymington, Hampshire, England":"Lymington, Hampshire, England","Basingstoke, Hampshire, England":"Basingstoke, Hampshire, England","England":"England","Popham, Hampshire, England":"Popham, Hampshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1156–4 November 1251":"environ 1156–4 novembre 1251","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1187–1251":"1187–1251","1187–Male":"1187–Décédé","1195–1225":"1195–1225","1156–1251":"1156–1251","4 November 1251":"